&lt;p&gt;High Dependency Unit&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Do you have experience of working in a critical care setting?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Do you want to work in the UKs newest and most technologically advanced heart centre?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Do you want the opportunity to participate in nurse-led research? Are you looking for a new opportunity…?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here is your chance to the new and expanding High dependency unit within the Adult critical care setting. A fantastic Opportunity has arisen band 5 staff nurse to be part of the delivery of world class health care&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our HDU cares for patients following a variety of complex cardiothoracic and cardiovascular procedures.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our education programs, supported by our practice education team, aim to provide support and development for all staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for highly motivated individual who has excellent care values, and a strong sense of team spirit to lead a team of nurses to deliver high quality care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are passionate and committed to the development and application of high quality patient care as we are, we want to hear from you!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameKeisha MillsEmail addresskeisha.mills@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
